<p class="MsoBodyText">Sir Roger yawned. He buffed his nails on a
silken sleeve. “What did he say?” he asked me.</p>
<p class="MsoBodyText">I told him. “Treachery,” I groaned. “We were
all supposed to be unarmed.”</p>
<p class="MsoBodyText">‘Nay, remember no oaths were sworn. But tell
his disgrace Duke Huruga that I foresaw this chance, and carry my
own protection.” The baron pressed the ornate seal ring on his
