feathery antennae, nor was there any possibility of issue between
her species and our own. But the humanlikeness, and exceeding
gratitude, of the Vashtunari-who had just been in process of being
conquered-did much to cheer lonely Englishmen. Whether or not the
prohibitions of Leviticus are applicable is still being hotly
debated.</p>
