selected one and pronounced it. From the corner of an eye, as I
squatted by the dials, I saw his jaw fall. He sank back into his
chair. I pronounced another English word for good measure.</p>
<p class="MsoBodyText">“Your honor lies in the well-being of your
people,” I added. “You’re not fit to judge anything which can so
shake you as this. Sit down and let me hear it.”</p>
